The original code redundantly calls both `list.find` and `list.index_of`. Since `list.index_of` already returns `None` when the element is absent and `Some(idx)` when found, the `list.find` call is unnecessary. Here is the refactored version:

```aiken
use aiken/collection/list
use aiken/crypto.{VerificationKeyHash}

fn signer_position(signers: List<VerificationKeyHash>, target: VerificationKeyHash) -> Option<Int> {
  list.index_of(signers, target)
}
```

`list.index_of` handles both the existence check and the position lookup in a single pass, making the helper function a clean one-liner.

